✅ Question 1

Task:
Get names of employees with salary > 50000, sorted by salary (descending)

✔ Solution:
SELECT name
FROM Employees
WHERE salary > 50000
ORDER BY salary DESC;


✅ Question 2

Task:
Find average salary per department

✔ Solution:
SELECT department, AVG(salary) AS avg_salary
FROM Employees
GROUP BY department;


✅ Question 3

Task:
Count employees in each department where count > 2

✔ Solution:
SELECT department, COUNT(*) AS employee_count
FROM Employees
GROUP BY department
HAVING COUNT(*) > 2;


✅ Question 4

Task:
Find highest salary in each department

✔ Solution:
SELECT department, MAX(salary) AS max_salary
FROM Employees
GROUP BY department;


✅ Question 5

Task:
Find departments where average salary > 55000

✔ Solution:
SELECT department, AVG(salary) AS avg_salary
FROM Employees
GROUP BY department
HAVING AVG(salary) > 55000;
